<%
  set_meta_tags(
    title: "Introduction - Rails UI Components",
    description: "A comprehensive Rails 7 component library built with ViewComponent, TailwindCSS 4.0, and Stimulus.",
    keywords: "Rails, UI, Components, ViewComponent, TailwindCSS, Stimulus"
  )
%>

<article class="space-y-8">
  <header class="space-y-4">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900">Rails UI Component Library</h1>
    <p class="text-xl text-gray-600">
      A comprehensive Rails 7 component library built with ViewComponent, TailwindCSS 4.0, and Stimulus.
      This template provides a complete set of reusable UI components that developers can copy and customize for their projects.
    </p>
  </header>

  <section class="space-y-6">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900">Overview</h2>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
      <div class="p-6 rounded-lg bg-blue-50">
        <h3 class="mb-3 text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900">Component-Based Architecture</h3>
        <p class="text-blue-700">
          Built with ViewComponent for server-side component rendering, providing better organization and reusability.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="p-6 rounded-lg bg-green-50">
        <h3 class="mb-3 text-lg font-semibold text-green-900">Modern Styling</h3>
        <p class="text-green-700">
          Uses TailwindCSS 4.0 with utility-first approach and custom component styles for complex interactions.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="p-6 rounded-lg bg-purple-50">
        <h3 class="mb-3 text-lg font-semibold text-purple-900">Interactive Behavior</h3>
        <p class="text-purple-700">
          Stimulus controllers provide client-side behavior while maintaining Rails conventions and simplicity.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="p-6 rounded-lg bg-orange-50">
        <h3 class="mb-3 text-lg font-semibold text-orange-900">Turbo Compatible</h3>
        <p class="text-orange-700">
          Works seamlessly with Turbo Drive and Frames for SPA-like experience without JavaScript complexity.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="space-y-4">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900">What's Included</h2>

